Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Stigma
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09pmbdf
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 5 Feb 2018
Stigma - Laurie Taylor explores the origins and meaning of Erving Goffman's famous sociological concept and the ways it's being re-cast by social scientists in the 21st century. He's joined by Graham Scambler, Emeritus Professor of Sociology at University College, London, Lisa Morris, Lecturer in Social Work at the University of Birmingham and Joanna Latimer, Professor of Sociology at the University of York. Producer: Jayne Egerton. Show less